      <li>A <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">div</code> with class <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">activity-stat</code> where the acivityâ€™s stat will be shown</li>
      <li>A <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">div</code> with class <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">activity-button</code> where will we make a button so that we can interact with that activity</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>You can see in the HTML that the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">activity-icon</code>s donâ€™t have anything in their <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">src</code> attribute. Letâ€™s go ahead and find icons to represent each of our activities: food, water, and exercise. After find those icons, download them into your <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">virtual-pet</code> folder and name them appropriately. Then, change the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">src</code> attribute in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">img</code>s to match the images you have downloaded.</p>

